[SN]TITLE[SN]
Teenage boys had taken prescription medication say police

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Four teenage boys who were admitted to hospital in Londonderry had taken prescription medication.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
They were brought to Altnagelvin Hospital on Wednesday evening after becoming unwell.
Three boys are in a stable condition. The condition of the fourth boy has not been released at the request of his family.
A police spokesperson warned that medication should not be taken without clinical advice.
"In general, our advice is that any drugs or medication taken without medical advice can be harmful," a police spokesperson said.
"If anyone does become ill, they should seek medical attention immediately."
